By midnight, the apartment was quiet again. Barnaby sat on the floor, surrounded by his broken dreams and a very confused cat. He took out his notebook and wrote: Note to self: Bacon is a hazardus projectile. He smiled, knowing that tomorow would be another chance to build something amazing. After all, an inventer never truely quits; they just recalibrate.